The Young Prophet and The Dragons, Part 1 (*RP*)<br>
-------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
*ooc* Ok, here's Part 1 of Prav's interpretation of an RP encounter that happened over the weekend. Note, I said _PRAV'S_ interpretation. That's because I'm dropping some things said, and changing others - Prav hears what he wants to hear (and also what I notice in the insanity of the moment. *chuckle*). Anyone who would like a copy of the actual log, just let me know and I'll be glad to send it to you.<br>
<br>
======================================<br>
<br>
The Prophet realized he needed some trade supplies, and headed out to Freeport. When he got there, Atoxus offered to show him a shortcut. The young prophet then followed the messenger's lead and walked the streets. As he walked the paths, he was about to mention that this looked more like the way to the Arena rather than the Trader's Holiday when he heard a noise.<br>
<br>
&quot;...No idea...&quot;<br>
<br>
That voice - it almost sounded like the half-breed named Minz. The prophet looked about and saw them all sitting there in front of the arena.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well, well, well,&quot; The young Prophet said. &quot;Look at the pretty little salamanders.&quot; The half-breed growled at the prophet as his motley crew of lightdwellers grumbled and said things like, &quot;Alas, more filth.&quot;<br>
<br>
The prophet couldn't help himself he looked at Minz and chuckled at the hatred washing forth. One of them had the audacity to laugh at the priest as the half-breed said, &quot;The city crawls with Drow.&quot;<br>
<br>
The prophet only smiled sweetly and said, &quot;Any message for the little bard?&quot; The looks in their eyes caused him to smirk in merriment at it all.<br>
<br>
&quot;Tell her we shall see her soon,&quot; the half-breed countered calmly as the one named Quezex challenged the priest to a duel. The prophet ignored the challenge as he had more important things to tend to, and besides, if he still wanted to after he knew the consequences, then the prophet would oblige him gladly.<br>
<br>
&quot;And I make the same offer to you as I did to Xareth.&quot; The half-breed continued.<br>
<br>
&quot;Here let me carve it in your back,&quot; the one Atoxus said was named Nrain threatened with a look in his eyes as though he truly meant it.<br>
<br>
The half-breed continued on and said, &quot;We offer our aid to seeking the cure. Hold Nrain, be still.&quot;<br>
<br>
The paladin seethed at the ignoring of his challenge, so the Prophet continued to ignore him and said, &quot;Oh? Your aid you say? I've seen enough aid from your dear friend Kassy.&quot;<br>
<br>
The one who had made for the perfect patsy - the prophet thought his name was Legodus...Logulus...something like that - said, &quot;You would aid such as these? Why? They are not worthy of our notice, let alone our aid.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;We shall see her,&quot; the half-breed said, &quot;Because it is the right thing to do.&quot;<br>
<br>
The Prophet laughed at the half-breed while some pompous bard with a red shield tried to play more soothing music. He then said amidst his chuckles, &quot;Fool - I no longer care of a cure...I am...enjoying...having her as my guest,&quot; he said as he licked his lips.<br>
<br>
The patsy said, &quot;The only right thing to do is to kill them. Slowly.&quot; Another of the little salamanders said, &quot;Who let a scum like you wander around here?&quot;<br>
<br>
The half-breed gritted his teeth as the Prophet continued on and said, &quot;Know this, as I said to Kassy...&quot; He looked out at them all as they whispered and grumbled and then continued on. &quot;You may very well take my life. However, my actions shall ensure my return.&quot;<br>
<br>
The patsy said, &quot;Oh, I WILL take more than that, I can promise you&quot;<br>
<br>
Another spoke up and said, &quot;I would enjoy that, but even death is too good for you&quot;<br>
<br>
The prophet had paused to let them voice their boasts and then said, &quot;And then I will see to the pretty little bard 10 times over.&quot; <br>
